Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of a communication system with limited channel state information feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of a single-antenna channel and the investigation of the impact of feedback delay suggest a focus on networked systems (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The study of the ergodic and outage performance also involves the evaluation of the diversity-multiplexing tradeoffs, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
